01:15:14,248 --> 01:15:16,182
Ok. Bye

832
01:16:14,775 --> 01:16:16,436
Bhairav Singh

833
01:16:17,845 --> 01:16:19,335
l am coming to get you...

834
01:16:21,715 --> 01:16:23,774
Do you understand recession?

835
01:16:24,318 --> 01:16:25,785
Disgraceful.

836
01:16:56,283 --> 01:16:57,477
Was this picnic your idea?

837
01:16:58,819 --> 01:17:01,344
Your father isn't as bad
as you make him out to be.

838
01:17:02,223 --> 01:17:06,057
l just don't get him.
Sometimes a demon, sometimes a lamb.

839
01:17:07,828 --> 01:17:10,023
Spoken like a true writer...

840
01:17:11,098 --> 01:17:12,360
l'm not talking like a writer...

841
01:17:13,100 --> 01:17:16,433
Your mother would have been
proud if she were alive today.

842
01:17:16,971 --> 01:17:18,836
She always wanted you
to be a writer.

843
01:17:19,173 --> 01:17:20,367
Really?
- Yes.

844
01:17:21,442 --> 01:17:24,900
She never told your
father but she told me...

845
01:17:25,846 --> 01:17:30,783
How she would've loved that line...
Sometimes a demon, sometimes a lamb.

846
01:17:33,454 --> 01:17:38,118
Sometimes a demon,
sometimes a lamb.

847
01:17:38,192 --> 01:17:40,854
Stop it!

848
01:17:50,004 --> 01:17:53,405
l have an idea...

849
01:17:53,474 --> 01:17:55,465
What is it?

850
01:17:57,978 --> 01:17:59,309
Let's hear one of Rohan's poems...

851
01:18:04,151 --> 01:18:06,016
He's written a full-length novel...

852
01:18:07,488 --> 01:18:10,548
l'm not asking you to
change your mind ...

853
01:18:11,158 --> 01:18:14,491
Listen to it. lf you
don't like it, don't applaud.

854
01:18:18,032 --> 01:18:20,159
Come on big man, go for it.

855
01:18:24,505 --> 01:18:29,499
lf you could see past the shore,
You would know what l think.

856
01:18:30,444 --> 01:18:35,177
lf you could hear the waves,
You would know what l think.

857
01:18:36,317 --> 01:18:41,118
Remove your veil of obstinacy,
And look beyond the window.

858
01:18:42,056 --> 01:18:46,584
lf you could see through convention,
You would know what l think.

859
01:18:47,861 --> 01:18:52,889
lf you had faith in yourself as l do,
You could walk with me a while...

860
01:18:53,934 --> 01:18:58,428
lf you could see the colors l do,
You could walk with me a while.

861
01:18:59,473 --> 01:19:01,873
lf you want to touch the sky as l do,

862
01:19:01,942 --> 01:19:04,172
Then your desires would come alive.

863
01:19:04,945 --> 01:19:09,609
Then, in my next life, we
could fly together a while.

864
01:19:17,424 --> 01:19:18,482
Forget it

865
01:19:19,493 --> 01:19:20,892
A woman's magazine will publish it...

866
01:19:20,961 --> 01:19:23,259
...or someone will drop a
coin in your begging bowl.

867
01:20:11,879 --> 01:20:12,937
Hello.

868
01:20:15,983 --> 01:20:17,041
Please... sit...

869
01:20:17,684 --> 01:20:18,742
Hello

870
01:20:18,819 --> 01:20:19,877
How are you?
- Please, have a seat.

871
01:20:19,953 --> 01:20:21,011
How was the journey?

872
01:20:21,355 --> 01:20:23,323
Okay. Our flight got a bit delayed.

873
01:20:24,892 --> 01:20:26,416
l made these for you to read.

874
01:20:50,384 --> 01:20:55,117
They're good...

875
01:20:56,323 --> 01:20:58,018
l'm glad you came today.

876
01:20:59,059 --> 01:21:00,390
l'm off to Kolkata tomorrow...

877
01:21:00,861 --> 01:21:03,455
Let me show you the workshop.

878
01:21:04,264 --> 01:21:05,322
Sure.

879
01:21:10,871 --> 01:21:11,929
Hello?

880
01:21:12,005 --> 01:21:13,472
ls that Mr. Singh?
- Yes?

881
01:21:13,807 --> 01:21:17,174
l'm Mrs Batra here,
Principal of Arjun's school.

882
01:21:17,244 --> 01:21:18,802
Yes Mrs Batra, tell me.

883
01:21:18,879 --> 01:21:22,007
There's been another problem with
your son, Arjun, this morning...

884
01:21:22,816 --> 01:21:25,785
We'd like you to come here
and take him back home today.

885
01:21:27,020 --> 01:21:30,012
l'm in a meeting right now.
Can l come post lunch?

886
01:21:30,290 --> 01:21:33,088
No Mr. Singh. This is an
extremely serious problem.

887
01:21:33,160 --> 01:21:34,252
l know Mrs. Batra but...

888
01:21:35,362 --> 01:21:37,125
Keep him in your office for sometime.

889
01:21:37,197 --> 01:21:38,755
Mr. Singh please understand

890
01:21:38,832 --> 01:21:41,096
l cannot allow Arjun to
remain in school today.

891
01:21:42,102 --> 01:21:44,366
Okay, l'm coming.

892
01:21:44,438 --> 01:21:45,496
ln half an hour?

893
01:21:45,572 --> 01:21:46,903
Yes Mrs. Batra. l'm coming right now.

894
01:21:46,974 --> 01:21:48,032
Thank you, Mr. Singh.

895
01:21:51,378 --> 01:21:55,508
l'm sorry, but l have to
rush to my son's school.

896
01:21:55,849 --> 01:21:59,182
He's been unwell
recently and it got worse today.

897
01:21:59,253 --> 01:22:03,121
But Mr. Rao will show
you around the workshop.

898
01:22:03,190 --> 01:22:05,852
No problem. We'll come back tomorrow.

899
01:22:05,926 --> 01:22:08,190
We have other factories to see today.

900
01:22:08,328 --> 01:22:12,025
But l told you, l have to be in
Kolkata tomorrow. l've committed it.

901
01:22:12,466 --> 01:22:14,525
l am sorry. We can't stay any longer.

902
01:22:15,402 --> 01:22:18,428
Anyway. We'll meet again.
Some other time?

903
01:22:19,139 --> 01:22:20,197
Okay...

904
01:22:20,407 --> 01:22:21,465
Let's go.

905
01:22:51,905 --> 01:22:52,963
What happened?

906
01:22:53,173 --> 01:22:54,231
Get in the car.

907
01:23:13,393 --> 01:23:14,451
What happened?

908
01:23:15,862 --> 01:23:17,022
His blood pressure is very low.

909
01:23:17,531 --> 01:23:19,431
Seems like he's had a bad fall.

910
01:23:20,200 --> 01:23:21,497
There could be internal bleeding.

911
01:23:22,336 --> 01:23:25,237
l'll have to check. We'll keep him
under observation for a few days.

912
01:23:25,305 --> 01:23:26,363
How many days?

913
01:23:26,940 --> 01:23:27,998
Four to five days.

914
01:23:28,075 --> 01:23:29,133
Four to five days?

915
01:23:29,209 --> 01:23:32,235
Don't worry. He'll
be fine. Don't worry.

916
01:23:33,146 --> 01:23:34,204
Thank you.

917
01:23:37,884 --> 01:23:38,942
How did it happen?

918
01:23:39,486 --> 01:23:40,544
Fell down the stairs.

919
01:23:41,955 --> 01:23:43,013
How?

920
01:23:43,423 --> 01:23:45,948
How should l know? He just fell.

921
01:23:50,230 --> 01:23:51,629
You go home. l'll stay here.

922
01:23:52,966 --> 01:23:54,024
l'm also staying.

923
01:23:58,572 --> 01:23:59,630
What happened to your results?

924
01:24:00,907 --> 01:24:02,636
l passed.
- Marks?

925
01:24:03,977 --> 01:24:06,036
They're good.
- Good.

926
01:24:14,521 --> 01:24:16,113
l'm going to Kolkata for three days.

927
01:24:18,258 --> 01:24:21,159
lf all goes well, l'll
return with a few contracts.

928
01:24:22,262 --> 01:24:24,162
You stay here with Arjun.

929
01:24:24,464 --> 01:24:26,989
And don't leave him alone, okay?

930
01:24:27,067 --> 01:24:28,125
Yes Sir.

931
01:24:33,473 --> 01:24:34,531
And...

932
01:24:35,075 --> 01:24:37,134
No need to inform Uncle and Auntie.

933
01:24:38,278 --> 01:24:41,679
l've told them that both of
you are going with me. Okay?

934
01:24:42,015 --> 01:24:43,073
Yes Sir.

935
01:24:45,419 --> 01:24:46,477
Fine.

936
01:24:56,296 --> 01:24:57,354
Have you eaten?

937
01:25:04,638 --> 01:25:06,037
Sir has gone to kolkata.

938
01:25:08,575 --> 01:25:09,633
Aren't you happy?

939
01:25:18,185 --> 01:25:19,243
What happened yesterday?

940
01:25:48,281 --> 01:25:49,339
For you.

941
01:25:57,023 --> 01:25:58,081
And these...

942
01:25:58,158 --> 01:25:59,750
lf you feel like reading.

943
01:26:08,235 --> 01:26:10,635
This has my poems and stories.

944
01:26:11,304 --> 01:26:12,362
Would you like to hear some?

945
01:26:16,643 --> 01:26:17,701
Hello Arjun.

946
01:26:19,446 --> 01:26:20,572
Are you feeling well today?

947
01:26:21,281 --> 01:26:22,339
Good.

948
01:26:28,321 --> 01:26:29,583
Could you change his clothes?

949
01:26:29,656 --> 01:26:31,123
Yes.
- Thank you.

950
01:26:35,662 --> 01:26:36,720
What is it?

951
01:27:06,092 --> 01:27:07,150
What now?

952
01:28:06,152 --> 01:28:11,146
Lunch was to be served by 12.30.
lts 1 :00 p.m now.

953
01:28:11,224 --> 01:28:13,158
Please don't shout. lt's bad for you.

954
01:28:13,226 --> 01:28:14,454
Yes l know.

955
01:28:14,761 --> 01:28:16,160
l can get a heart attack.

956
01:28:16,229 --> 01:28:18,322
But if l die of hunger before that?

957
01:28:18,398 --> 01:28:20,457
l'll go and get your food just now.

958
01:28:20,901 --> 01:28:22,163
Get it fast...

959
01:28:22,702 --> 01:28:24,897
Corpses don't eat.

960
01:28:29,776 --> 01:28:30,902
Why don't you laugh?

961
01:28:32,379 --> 01:28:33,505
l am 80 years old...

962
01:28:34,514 --> 01:28:35,913
Grandfather of six.

963
01:28:36,416 --> 01:28:37,713
Great grandfather of two...

964
01:28:38,184 --> 01:28:39,242
Can't l shout?

965
01:28:40,186 --> 01:28:41,244
Laugh.

966
01:28:42,188 --> 01:28:43,246
Laugh.

967
01:28:58,638 --> 01:28:59,696
Would you like to listen to a poem?

968
01:29:10,817 --> 01:29:11,875
Chandu's Cycle.

969
01:29:12,752 --> 01:29:15,220
Chandu's cycle was
just like Chandu...

970
01:29:15,822 --> 01:29:18,689
As it moved, it crickered and
crankered, just like Chandu.

971
01:29:19,559 --> 01:29:22,619
The handle was as light
as Chandu's slender hand.

972
01:29:23,229 --> 01:29:26,255
The pedals were as thin
as Chandu's spindle legs.

973
01:29:27,233 --> 01:29:30,225
The seat was as broad
as Chandu's huge behind.

974
01:29:30,971 --> 01:29:34,236
The carrier was as small
as Chandu's short career.

975
01:29:34,774 --> 01:29:36,366
Yet it was Chandu's true friend.

976
01:29:36,843 --> 01:29:38,276
Was always loyal to Chandu.

977
01:29:39,245 --> 01:29:42,772
lt took Chandu's
heavy weight with ease.

978
01:29:43,350 --> 01:29:46,786
One day the cycle broke down.

979
01:29:47,253 --> 01:29:49,244
Seeing a bull charging at him,

980
01:29:49,356 --> 01:29:50,687
Chandu dropped it hard.

981
01:29:51,257 --> 01:29:54,249
When Monty Mechanic
could not save the cycle,

982
01:29:54,928 --> 01:29:58,261
Chandu's father sold
it to a scrap dealer.

983
01:29:58,732 --> 01:30:02,259
Chandu drowned himself in his books.

984
01:30:02,402 --> 01:30:05,371
Like he had an old dream to fulfill.

985
01:30:06,006 --> 01:30:07,405
Later, when Chandu grew up,

986
01:30:07,807 --> 01:30:09,274
He used his very first salary...

987
01:30:09,676 --> 01:30:13,271
And got himself a new cycle...

988
01:30:14,280 --> 01:30:15,338
But...

989
01:30:15,515 --> 01:30:16,573
But?

990
01:30:16,816 --> 01:30:20,274
This cycle too was
just like Chandu...

991
01:30:20,620 --> 01:30:23,282
lt still crickered and
crankered as it moved around.

992
01:30:23,823 --> 01:30:25,290
lt's seat was...

993
01:30:25,358 --> 01:30:27,417
As broad as Chandu's huge behind.

994
01:30:27,627 --> 01:30:29,288
The carrier was as small...

995
01:30:29,362 --> 01:30:31,296
As Chandu's short career.

996
01:30:34,300 --> 01:30:35,358
You wrote that?

997
01:30:36,536 --> 01:30:38,299
Yes
- Wow...

998
01:30:38,972 --> 01:30:40,030
Very good.

999
01:30:40,907 --> 01:30:42,306
Very inspiring !

1000
01:30:42,542 --> 01:30:44,976
Thank you.
- Keep writing like this, son.

1001
01:30:45,712 --> 01:30:47,043
Keep writing.

1002
01:30:48,381 --> 01:30:50,975
Write.

1003
01:30:59,926 --> 01:31:02,918
How many friends do
you have in school?

1004
01:31:06,332 --> 01:31:07,390
Seven.

1005
01:31:07,467 --> 01:31:08,525
Their names?

1006
01:31:08,735 --> 01:31:09,793
Apurva,

1007
01:31:10,336 --> 01:31:11,735
Sunny, Raju,

1008
01:31:11,805 --> 01:31:13,329
Batuk, Kunal...

1009
01:31:13,573 --> 01:31:15,507
Kunal...Kunal,

1010
01:31:15,575 --> 01:31:16,633
Veer.

1011
01:31:17,343 --> 01:31:18,401
And?

1012
01:31:18,611 --> 01:31:19,669
And...

1013
01:31:20,880 --> 01:31:21,938
That's only six.

1014
01:31:24,350 --> 01:31:25,544
And one more...

1015
01:31:26,820 --> 01:31:27,878
Tushar.

1016
01:31:28,354 --> 01:31:29,685
You have so many friends.

1017
01:31:30,356 --> 01:31:31,550
l have only three.

1018
01:31:32,892 --> 01:31:34,416
What was your mother like?

1019
01:31:35,361 --> 01:31:37,727
My mother was very nice.

1020
01:31:38,965 --> 01:31:40,432
She loved me a lot.

1021
01:31:41,367 --> 01:31:42,595
She smelled wonderful

1022
01:31:42,669 --> 01:31:44,364
when l'd cuddle up to sleep.

1023
01:31:45,038 --> 01:31:46,369
Just like a mother.

1024
01:31:48,475 --> 01:31:50,443
l don't know what
my mother was like.

1025
01:31:51,044 --> 01:31:52,375
Do you know her?

1026
01:31:53,980 --> 01:31:55,038
No.

1027
01:32:02,722 --> 01:32:03,780
Mr Poet...

1028
01:32:06,392 --> 01:32:07,620
Why don't you ever laugh?

1029
01:32:08,995 --> 01:32:10,053
Yes.

1030
01:32:10,130 --> 01:32:12,394
Look at you now. You look so good.

1031
01:32:14,000 --> 01:32:15,399
When do we hear something new?

1032
01:32:15,702 --> 01:32:16,760
Tonight?

1033
01:32:16,936 --> 01:32:17,994
ln the night?

1034
01:32:18,738 --> 01:32:20,000
Do you also write at night?

1035
01:32:20,406 --> 01:32:21,464
Sometimes.

1036
01:32:21,541 --> 01:32:22,667
Beware of the night ...

1037
01:32:23,476 --> 01:32:24,534
You see ...

1038
01:32:24,878 --> 01:32:26,402
The day destroys the night,

1039
01:32:26,746 --> 01:32:28,008
Night divides the day.

1040
01:32:28,581 --> 01:32:29,639
Try to run,

1041
01:32:29,949 --> 01:32:31,007
Try to hide...

1042
01:32:31,151 --> 01:32:32,550
Break on through to the other side.

1043
01:32:35,488 --> 01:32:38,423
This is the true
story of three friends...

1044
01:32:38,691 --> 01:32:41,421
Muninder, Benoy and Rohit.

1045
01:32:41,795 --> 01:32:45,424
The kingdom where
they lived would select

1046
01:32:45,498 --> 01:32:47,432
the smartest boys for training.

1047
01:32:47,767 --> 01:32:52,033
Years later, they would join
the King's prestigious army.

1048
01:32:52,705 --> 01:32:56,436
But nobody really knew what
went on inside the castle.

1049
01:32:56,976 --> 01:33:00,434
Their parents didn't know
that the King's evil minister,

1050
01:33:00,513 --> 01:33:03,880
Was brain-washing the kids
and turning them into robots.

1051
01:33:04,184 --> 01:33:05,446
ls it a true story?

1052
01:33:05,518 --> 01:33:06,576
Yes.

1053
01:33:06,653 --> 01:33:09,451
The wicked man's name was Rathod.

1054
01:33:09,522 --> 01:33:10,580
Rathod!

1055
01:33:10,657 --> 01:33:11,851
Yes, Rathod.

1056
01:34:16,055 --> 01:34:18,148
Vikreet and Benoy were
with the full Robot Army...

1057
01:34:18,524 --> 01:34:20,515
Muninder and the kids
were due any minute now...

1058
01:34:20,827 --> 01:34:23,819
Rohit was worried.
They hadn't come yet.

1059
01:34:24,264 --> 01:34:28,530
He turned around. And froze.
A terrified look came into his eyes.

1060
01:34:29,202 --> 01:34:31,193
He saw someone
coming through the tunnel.

1061
01:34:31,871 --> 01:34:33,668
Someone was coming from the tunnel...

1062
01:34:33,740 --> 01:34:34,866
Who was coming?

1063
01:34:38,778 --> 01:34:40,211
Who was it?

1064
01:34:46,152 --> 01:34:48,177
We'll finish tomorrow...
- Now!

1065
01:34:54,894 --> 01:34:56,020
34 in Chemistry

1066
01:34:57,563 --> 01:34:59,690
20 in Physics. 15 in Maths.

1067
01:35:01,034 --> 01:35:02,558
You told me you passed.

1068
01:35:04,170 --> 01:35:08,231
ls this a joke to you?

1069
01:35:09,642 --> 01:35:12,577
l thought you'd finally
become serious about your studies.

1070
01:35:12,645 --> 01:35:17,105
You're narrating
stories to half-dead people.

1071
01:35:17,183 --> 01:35:18,582
Just to hear them tell you
what a good writer you are.

1072
01:35:20,586 --> 01:35:21,644
What are you staring at?

1073
01:35:22,588 --> 01:35:23,646
Lower your eyes.

1074
01:35:24,991 --> 01:35:27,255
lf this wasn't a hospital,
l would skin you right now.

1075
01:35:28,594 --> 01:35:31,586
l'm not going to
forget this in a hurry.

1076
01:35:32,899 --> 01:35:36,835
Come home. l'll make
sure l get an answer.

1077
01:35:44,277 --> 01:35:45,608
What did Sir say?

1078
01:35:45,745 --> 01:35:48,612
Sir said that he will send
me to the hospital as well.

1079
01:35:48,748 --> 01:35:49,806
Why?

1080
01:35:50,683 --> 01:35:51,809
Because l failed my exams.

1081
01:35:53,319 --> 01:35:55,617
So you'll go back to
boarding school?

1082
01:35:56,155 --> 01:35:57,213
No. Why?

1083
01:35:57,290 --> 01:36:01,920
Sir said if l don't pass,
he'll send me to a boarding school.

1084
01:37:19,705 --> 01:37:21,036
What happened that day?

1085
01:37:22,375 --> 01:37:23,706
Sir hit me.

1086
01:37:25,711 --> 01:37:26,769
Why?

1087
01:37:26,846 --> 01:37:31,306
Two boys were teasing me at school.
l broke one's teeth.

1088
01:37:33,719 --> 01:37:34,777
Did he beat you a lot?

1089
01:37:34,854 --> 01:37:36,719
He beat me with a belt.

1090
01:38:32,245 --> 01:38:33,303
Shall we go?

1091
01:38:48,461 --> 01:38:49,792
How old are you?

1092
01:38:57,970 --> 01:38:59,494
l'm asking you something.

1093
01:39:00,406 --> 01:39:01,464
How old are you?

1094
01:39:03,809 --> 01:39:04,867
Seventeen.

1095
01:39:05,811 --> 01:39:06,869
